  "problem": {
    "fact": "Every selected target candidate had weak or partial base support and missing strong own-view evidence before active re-observation. The detector/SAM2 substrate now provides candidate-centered own-view recheck evidence for all 20 target candidates, but three frame rows have no candidate association.",
    "failure_mechanism": "Missing own-view support is a decision-uncertainty signal, not a valid-goal rejection rule. The analyzer must test whether active mobility acquired independent own-view support before the deferred negative_missing_support_guard can be interpreted.",
    "agent_inference": "A useful branch outcome would show that missing-own-view uncertainty can be converted into evidence state, but it still cannot establish ObjectNav goal validity without a later label-free arbitration rule."
  },
